      "comment": "MILES OF GLORY (4) wound up nicely second-up with a respectable third over 1300m at Goulburn. Raced in Group company last prep and gives the indication she's ready for the 1600m. Leading player.  VILLA CASTINA (6) progressive filly who knocked-up late on resumption when fourth over 1300m at Goulburn in the soft (7) going. Ran a respectable fifth in the LR Dulcify last October. Strips fitter and expected to measure up. SERPICO (5) fast finishing first-up winner, then went back from the outside draw with a battling sixth over 1300m at Wyong. Can race a touch closer from the good gate and has solid top-three claims. RIBBLE LACE (3) big jump in class and trip with a fading eighth over 2000m at Hawkesbury in BM68 company. Assess on the good win two-back and goes into the exotics.",
